# shellcheck shell=bash
# shellcheck disable=SC2034  # consumed by code that sources this file
# (lib/version-managers/node, and anything else that needs the pins).

# vmgr - node toolchain pins.
#
# These pins govern ONLY what `vmgr` installs and sets as the default; they
# do not constrain nvm itself. You can still run nvm directly to install,
# switch, or default any Node version you like.
#
#   - Fresh machine: `vmgr install node` clones this nvm release, installs
#     this Node version, and makes it the default.
#   - Bump a pin: `vmgr update node` brings an existing install to the new
#     pins (and `install` does too). Either RESETS the default Node to
#     NODE_PIN even when newer versions are installed - intentional
#     (idempotent toward the pins). Use nvm directly to set a different
#     default.
#
# The numbers live here (config, $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/vmgr/node) not in
# lib/version-managers/node, so they are set in ONE place and sourceable by
# anything that needs them. Bump deliberately.

# nvm release to install / pin to (git tag).
NVM_PIN=v0.40.5

# Exact Node version vmgr installs and sets as the default. Pinned (NOT a
# floating major like `22`) so a repeat `vmgr install node` does not pull a
# newer patch and the default it sets is deterministic.
NODE_PIN=v22.23.1
